  <li>
    <p>Part three - Random thoughts</p>
  </li>
  <li>Big macs vs naked chef = Consulting vs Product development organization
    <ul>
      <li>It is hard to scale talent. To scale talent creates rule and dumb follows.</li>
      <li>There is always a trade-off between quantity and quality.</li>
    </ul>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>NIH syndrome/Reinventing wheel is bad. Always think to built a layer on top of existing one.</p>
  </li>
  <li>Ben &amp; Jerry‚Äôs v/s Amazon = Organic growth vs Get Big fast</li>
</ul>

<table>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th>Ben &amp; Jerry‚Äôs</th>
      <th>Amazon</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td>No network effect, weak customer lock-in</td>
      <td>Strong network effect, strong customer lock-in</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Little capital required; break even fast</td>
      <td>Outrageous amounts of capital required; profitability can take years</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Corporate culture is important.</td>
      <td>Corporate culture is impossible.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Mistakes become valuable lessons.</td>
      <td>Mistakes are not really noticed.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>You‚Äôll probably succeed. You certainly won‚Äôt lose too much money.</td>
      <td>You have a tiny chance of becoming a billionaire, and a high chance of just failing.</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>It takes a long time to get big.</td>
      <td>You get big very fast.</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
